WEBVTT

00:01:20.120 --> 00:01:21.280
Just a minute.

00:02:45.600 --> 00:02:49.400
FRIENDS FOREVER REST IN PEACE

00:02:59.600 --> 00:03:00.680
Hey, Chit.

00:03:00.800 --> 00:03:02.120
Hi, Chang.

00:03:02.240 --> 00:03:03.200
How are you?

00:03:03.360 --> 00:03:04.320
How are you?

00:03:14.000 --> 00:03:15.200
Hi, Chit.

00:03:22.600 --> 00:03:26.160
That's the wrong note. Higher.
Breathe using your diaphragm.

00:03:29.480 --> 00:03:33.360
This is as far as I can help you.
The rest is up to you.

00:03:39.040 --> 00:03:42.240
Professor, this is my friend, Chit.

00:03:42.320 --> 00:03:43.720
Chit, this is Professor Winai.

00:03:43.760 --> 00:03:45.120
Afternoon, sir.

00:03:47.320 --> 00:03:50.520
He wants to talk
about the brass instruments.

00:03:51.520 --> 00:03:53.560
Oh, yes, come on in.

00:03:53.600 --> 00:03:54.680
Thank you.

00:03:55.800 --> 00:03:58.280
-Let's take a look.
-Here it is.

00:03:59.080 --> 00:03:59.880
Well…

00:03:59.960 --> 00:04:03.080
I heard a student playing on the trumpet

00:04:03.160 --> 00:04:06.520
and the sound quality wasn't that clear.

00:04:06.600 --> 00:04:09.320
I would like to recommend this one.

00:04:09.400 --> 00:04:10.360
You're from Yamaha?

00:04:11.120 --> 00:04:12.280
Yes, sir.

00:04:15.360 --> 00:04:16.200
Chang?

00:04:16.720 --> 00:04:21.360
I talked to Prame yesterday.

00:04:21.400 --> 00:04:22.480
Oh, really?

00:04:24.000 --> 00:04:29.000
I thought you were
from a different company.

00:04:29.440 --> 00:04:30.800
I can't help you.

00:04:31.040 --> 00:04:34.080
I'm about to place an order with Prame.

00:04:49.360 --> 00:04:51.160
Hi, Mom.

00:04:51.240 --> 00:04:53.040
<i>Hi, Chit. Have you eaten yet?</i>

00:04:53.120 --> 00:04:54.480
Yes, Mom.

00:04:54.560 --> 00:04:57.320
<i>Good. So what are you doing?</i>

00:04:58.080 --> 00:05:01.400
I’m on my way home. I’m almost there.

00:05:01.440 --> 00:05:05.360
<i>When you get there, try to rest, okay?</i>

00:05:06.320 --> 00:05:09.000
Yes, Mom. There's no need to worry.

00:05:09.080 --> 00:05:12.120
<i>Are you coming home</i>
<i>for the Songkran holidays?</i>

00:05:12.200 --> 00:05:13.680
<i>Everyone is asking about you.</i>

00:05:14.520 --> 00:05:17.720
I don’t know
if I can clear my work in time.

00:05:17.960 --> 00:05:19.600
I might need to do overtime.

00:05:19.680 --> 00:05:21.760
Everyone is very busy this time of year.

00:05:21.960 --> 00:05:24.160
Promotions are coming up.

00:05:24.760 --> 00:05:27.120
I might have the chance
to become a supervisor.

00:05:27.200 --> 00:05:28.400
Isn't that good?

00:05:29.240 --> 00:05:32.640
<i>Oh? That would be great.</i>

00:05:34.600 --> 00:05:38.440
But I’m sure I can come home
for a couple of days.

00:05:38.480 --> 00:05:40.160
<i>That’s good, son.</i>

00:05:40.240 --> 00:05:44.520
<i>If work is getting tough</i>
<i>then come home and relax.</i>

00:05:44.600 --> 00:05:48.160
<i>It worries me seeing you work so hard.</i>

00:05:48.240 --> 00:05:51.120
<i>If Bangkok is too hectic then come home.</i>

00:05:51.160 --> 00:05:52.040
Yes, Mom.

00:05:52.120 --> 00:05:54.520
<i>We may not be wealthy,</i>

00:05:54.560 --> 00:05:58.760
<i>but we'll be close.</i>
<i>We can take care of each other.</i>

00:06:02.400 --> 00:06:04.280
Yes, Mom. But don’t worry.

00:06:04.360 --> 00:06:06.960
Everything is coming along fine.

00:06:07.000 --> 00:06:08.240
<i>That's wonderful, son.</i>

00:06:08.280 --> 00:06:10.080
<i>And Maew, how is she doing?</i>

00:06:10.160 --> 00:06:13.040
<i>If you’re coming home, bring her along.</i>

00:06:13.120 --> 00:06:16.280
<i>She’s a famous singer now.</i>
<i>Has she’s forgotten me?</i>

00:06:16.360 --> 00:06:19.080
<i>Please tell her that we all miss her.</i>

00:06:19.160 --> 00:06:20.480
I will, Mom.

00:06:41.240 --> 00:06:43.640
HAPPY BIRTHDAY
"FOLLOW YOUR DREAMS" - PHUCHIT

00:06:43.720 --> 00:06:45.720
IN LOVE TO THE DREAMS…

00:07:18.400 --> 00:07:20.240
Sign here, please.

00:07:23.160 --> 00:07:25.040
What's this?

00:07:25.080 --> 00:07:26.680
You’ve missed
over three months of payments.

00:07:26.720 --> 00:07:30.320
Didn't you read the notices we sent?

00:07:30.360 --> 00:07:31.560
Sign here, too.

00:07:33.520 --> 00:07:34.680
Thank you.

00:07:37.120 --> 00:07:38.640
I'll need your keys too.

00:08:01.520 --> 00:08:04.480
-Hey, come stand here.
-Oh Tong! Hello!

00:08:06.560 --> 00:08:08.280
Don't get stuck in the middle.

00:08:09.120 --> 00:08:11.040
Why are you taking the bus?

00:08:11.120 --> 00:08:12.080
Need a change in scenery?

00:08:12.160 --> 00:08:14.040
Um, no.

00:08:14.760 --> 00:08:16.160
Hey, I brought your CD.

00:08:16.200 --> 00:08:18.320
But why?

00:08:18.400 --> 00:08:20.200
Don't you like the songs?
Don't you want the CD?

00:08:20.280 --> 00:08:21.320
No, it's not like that.

00:08:21.400 --> 00:08:23.760
You won't have to make
another copy to give to a studio.

00:08:24.000 --> 00:08:25.760
It'll save you some cash.

00:08:26.000 --> 00:08:28.080
I gave up that idea a long time ago.

00:08:28.120 --> 00:08:29.600
Go ahead, keep it.

00:08:29.680 --> 00:08:32.280
What record company would want these?

00:08:32.320 --> 00:08:35.560
I think your music is much better
than a lot of stuff nowadays.

00:08:37.360 --> 00:08:39.120
You’re just saying that.

00:08:42.320 --> 00:08:43.320
Seriously.

00:08:43.960 --> 00:08:46.280
Why don’t you give yourself a chance?

00:08:46.360 --> 00:08:49.440
Honestly, this internship is killing me.

00:08:49.520 --> 00:08:51.200
They use me like a full employee.

00:08:51.280 --> 00:08:53.560
So? Quit. Get the hell out.

00:08:53.600 --> 00:08:57.600
Are you crazy? My dad would kill me.

00:08:57.640 --> 00:09:00.960
You don't graduate in computers
to become a musician.

00:09:01.040 --> 00:09:03.480
Oh, so you want it like this then?

00:09:16.400 --> 00:09:19.960
When is Somboon taking us
for our bonus dinner?

00:09:20.040 --> 00:09:21.320
I have no idea.

00:09:21.400 --> 00:09:23.600
Is Somboon choosing the restaurant?

00:09:23.680 --> 00:09:25.280
Why doesn't he let Prame do it?

00:09:25.960 --> 00:09:28.680
The person with the best sales record
should choose.

00:09:28.760 --> 00:09:32.440
Exactly, if it wasn’t for Prame's sales,

00:09:32.520 --> 00:09:34.720
we wouldn’t even be getting a bonus.

00:09:34.800 --> 00:09:35.640
Yeah, that's true.

00:09:35.720 --> 00:09:39.360
-Prem, do you know how much the bonus is?
-Phuchit, is something bothering you?

00:09:40.240 --> 00:09:41.760
Oh, oh, nothing.

00:09:42.400 --> 00:09:44.440
Okay then, I’d better get to work.

00:09:44.520 --> 00:09:45.560
Okay.

00:10:23.160 --> 00:10:24.440
Hey, Prame?

00:10:24.520 --> 00:10:26.400
Oh, Chit. What's up?

00:10:27.160 --> 00:10:29.640
Did you make a sale over at St. Nicholas?

00:10:29.720 --> 00:10:32.640
Yes. Is something wrong?

00:10:33.400 --> 00:10:37.160
That school was one of my clients
and you knew it.

00:10:37.800 --> 00:10:39.440
Who is your contact?

00:10:39.480 --> 00:10:42.680
A friend. He's a teacher there.

00:10:42.760 --> 00:10:44.560
We've been talking about it for ages.

00:10:45.360 --> 00:10:47.280
-Why did you--
-Chit.

00:10:51.600 --> 00:10:53.240
You were too slow.

00:10:55.840 --> 00:11:00.360
Chit, Somboon wants to see you right away.

00:11:14.320 --> 00:11:15.600
It's okay, Am.

00:11:30.760 --> 00:11:31.800
Have a seat.

00:11:37.800 --> 00:11:39.200
Your documents…

00:11:58.600 --> 00:12:00.080
I don’t understand

00:12:00.120 --> 00:12:04.080
why your sales have been
dropping for the past three months,

00:12:04.960 --> 00:12:08.760
whereas everyone else
seems to be doing better.

00:12:09.400 --> 00:12:11.280
I’m trying, sir.

00:12:11.360 --> 00:12:15.360
Trying? Is this what you call trying?

00:12:17.120 --> 00:12:19.720
I think you misunderstand
the meaning of "trying".

00:12:20.440 --> 00:12:22.400
Take Prame, for example.

00:12:22.480 --> 00:12:24.320
That’s called trying.

00:12:25.520 --> 00:12:27.040
Excuse me, Mr. Somboon.

00:12:27.080 --> 00:12:30.320
The system is setup now. I need
to try to and access it from outside.

00:12:33.120 --> 00:12:36.360
Do you know what’s happening next month?

00:12:38.600 --> 00:12:41.480
We’re using our computer network?

00:12:41.560 --> 00:12:46.200
That’s right. We’re going online.

00:12:46.800 --> 00:12:48.440
There are many benefits to this system.

00:12:49.680 --> 00:12:52.440
It will let us work
more efficiently and effectively.

00:12:54.200 --> 00:12:56.080
Most importantly,

00:12:56.120 --> 00:12:58.560
it will lower our overheads,

00:12:59.320 --> 00:13:02.200
particularly those
that don’t generate profit.

00:13:09.560 --> 00:13:11.760
I really don’t want to do this to you.

00:13:13.160 --> 00:13:16.640
This resignation letter
will give you the opportunity

00:13:17.320 --> 00:13:20.360
to apply elsewhere
without getting a bad reference from us.

00:13:45.760 --> 00:13:48.760
DUNNING LETTER

00:14:11.600 --> 00:14:12.960
Thank you, Tong.

00:14:33.440 --> 00:14:34.640
Sorry.

00:14:40.400 --> 00:14:41.400
Hello, Mom.

00:14:41.480 --> 00:14:42.720
<i>Chit.</i>

00:14:43.640 --> 00:14:44.760
What is it, Mom?

00:14:45.000 --> 00:14:47.560
<i>Do you have 8000 Baht I could borrow?</i>

